Introduction  

ExoMars 2020 is an ESA -Roscosmos led mission which will investigate the presence of past and present  life on Mars. Equipped with a drill and a chemical analysis laboratory, it will be the first mission to sample  and analyses  the Martian underground down to two meters in depth.  

Figure 1: CLUPI Instrument mounted onto the ExoMars flight model{'source': 'AMS_2020.pdf', 'page': 69}

